    <section id="about">
        <h2>About Michael Jordan</h2>
        <p>Michael Jeffrey Jordan. Before Michael Jordan rose to NBA stardom and became an iconic figure in basketball history, his journey began in his
        hometown of Wilmington, North Carolina. Jordan's early years were marked by his deep passion for sports, particularly
        baseball and basketball. He showed immense promise as a high school basketball player, earning a spot on the varsity
        team during his sophomore year. His growth spurt in high school contributed to his development as a versatile and agile
        player, eventually earning him a scholarship to the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.
        <br>
        <br>
        At UNC, Jordan continued to hone his skills under the guidance of legendary coach Dean Smith. During his freshman year,
        he made a significant impact by sinking the game-winning shot in the NCAA championship game, illustrating his remarkable
        poise and clutch abilities even at a young age. His time at UNC saw him named ACC Player of the Year, and he later led
        the U.S. Men's Basketball Team to a gold medal at the 1984 Summer Olympics in Los Angeles. These early successes were
        pivotal in establishing Jordan as a highly sought-after prospect for the upcoming NBA Draft.
        <br>
        <br>
        The 1984 NBA Draft marked the next phase of Michael Jordan's journey as he was selected by the Chicago Bulls as the
        third overall pick. Little did the basketball world know that this unassuming rookie would go on to redefine the game,
        amass numerous accolades, and cement his legacy as one of the greatest basketball players of all time. Jordan's
        incredible work ethic, combined with the skills he had developed in his formative years, set the stage for a career that
        would not only transform the NBA but also transcend the world of sports.</p>
        
    </section>

